name: DNA-(apurinic or apyrimidinic site) lyase
reaction: The C-O-P bond 3' to the apurinic or apyrimidinic site in DNA is broken by a beta-elimination reaction, leaving a 3'-terminal unsaturated sugar and a product with a terminal 5'-phosphate
comment: 'Nicking' of the phosphodiester bond is due to a lyase-type reaction, not hydrolysis. This group of enzymes was previously listed as endonucleases, under EC 3.1.25.2.

orthologs.K10765: alkylated DNA repair protein alkB homolog 1

references.title: Bacteriophage-T4 and Micrococcus luteus UV endonucleases are not endonucleases but beta-elimination and sometimes beta delta-elimination catalysts.
Escherichia coli endonuclease III is not an endonuclease but a beta-elimination catalyst.
Mechanism of UV endonuclease-V cleavage of abasic sites in DNA determined by C-13 labeling.
